.TH "qla4xxx_abort_active_cmds" 9 "qla4xxx_abort_active_cmds" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qla4xxx_abort_active_cmds \- returns all outstanding i/o requests to O.S.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" qla4xxx_abort_active_cmds
.BI "(struct scsi_qla_host *ha "  ","
.BI "int res "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ha" 12
Pointer to host adapter structure.
.IP "res" 12
returned scsi status
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is called just prior to a HARD RESET to return all
outstanding commands back to the Operating System.
Caller should make sure that the following locks are released
before this calling routine: Hardware lock, and io_request_lock.
